description: With 12 V applied and the switch ON, use a voltmeter: (1) measure voltage between the two output terminals of the power supply module; (2) then, without changing any cables, measure voltage between the two input terminals of the control module, and finally between the two terminals at the load module. Record whether ~12 V is present at each point and note the polarity (which side is positive)., outcome='Measured relative to ground, the PSU Output (+), Control Input (+), and Load Input (+) cables are all at ~11.96 V, while the corresponding (−) cables are at ~0 V (within a few millivolts). No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED: all (+) cables are positive with respect to ground, and all (−) cables are near 0 V.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=120.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module lamps (main and indicator),
description: With 12 V applied and the switch ON, disconnect the load module from the rest of the system. Using a bench supply or the same 12 V source, apply 12 V directly across the load module input terminals (respecting polarity confirmed earlier) and observe whether the main lamp and the internal indicator lamp light. If neither lights with correct polarity and voltage present at the module terminals, suspect open/failed lamps or internal wiring in the load module., outcome='12 V is present at the Load Input Cable (+) and near 0 V at the Load Input Cable (−), with no polarity inversion indicated at the cables. The main load lamp is not lit and shows an extremely high internal resistance, while the internal indicator lamp is lit and shows no observable internal fault.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=305.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('verify_repair', 120.0), ('verify_repair', 120.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
